P(x)
n \geq 1
\int_{0}^{1}x^{k}P(x)\,dx = 0
k = 1, 2, \ldots, n
\int_{0}^{1}\{P(x)\}^{2}\,dx = (n + 1)^{2}\left(\int_{0}^{1}P(x)\,dx\right)^{2}
P(x) = a_{0}x^{n} + \cdots + a_{n - 1}x + a_{n}
a_{n}/(n + 1)^{2}
\int_{0}^{1}\{P(x)\}^{2}\,dx = a_{n}\int_{0}^{1}P(x)\,dx
\int_{0}^{1}P(x)\,dx = \frac{a_{n}}{(n + 1)^{2}}
\frac{a_{0}}{n + 1} + \frac{a_{1}}{n} + \cdots + \frac{a_{n - 1}}{2} + a_{n}
\displaystyle \int_0^1 x^kP(x)\,dx=\frac{a_0}{n+k+1}+\frac{a_1}{n+k}+\ldots+\frac{a_n}{k+1}=0
k=1,2,\ldots,n
f(x)=\dfrac{a_0}{n+x+1}+\dfrac{a_1}{n+x}+\ldots+\dfrac{a_n}{x+1}=\dfrac{Q(x)}{(n+x+1)\ldots(x+1)}
n
x=1,2,\ldots,n
Q(x)=c(x-1)(x-2)\ldots(x-n)
c
(x+1)f(x)=\dfrac{a_0(x+1)}{n+x+1}+\dfrac{a_1(x+1)}{n+x}+\ldots+a_n=\dfrac{Q(x)}{(n+x+1)\ldots(x+2)}
x=-1
a_n = \dfrac{Q(-1)}{n!}=\dfrac{c(-1)^n(n+1)!}{n!}=c(-1)^n(n+1)
x=0
\displaystyle \int_0^1 P(x)\,dx = \dfrac{a_0}{n+1}+\ldots+a_n=\dfrac{Q(0)}{(n+1)!}=\dfrac{c(-1)^n}{n+1}
a_n=\displaystyle (n+1)^2\int_0^1 P(x)\,dx
